==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lutetium
<hw>Lu*te"ti*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A metallic element separated from ytterbium in 1907, by
<person>Urbain</person> in Paris and by <person>von Welsbach</person> in
Vienna. It is a member of the Lanthanide <isa>rare earth</isa> group.
Symbol, <it>Lu</it>; atomic number 71; atomic weight 174.967 [C=12.011].
Previously spelled <asp>Lutecium</asp>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

